Module kivakit.interfaces

Package com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.collection

package com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.collection
  • Interfaces
    Class
    Description
    Addable<Value>
    An object, often a collection or related type, to which objects can be added.
    Appendable<Value>
    An object, often a collection or related type, to which objects can be appended.
    Clearable
    Interface to an object that can be cleared
    Contains<Value>
    An interface for any object that can contain values, typically a collection.
    Copyable<Value,Copy extends Addable<Value> & Sequence<Value>>
    Makes a copy of a given sequence
    Emptiness
    Identifies whether an object, such as a collection, is empty or non-empty.
    Indexable<Value>
    A sequence that has a known size and can be indexed, like a list, although not necessarily a collection.
    Indexed
    An object which has an index.
    Joinable<Value>
    An object that is Joinable is Iterable.
    Keyed<Key,Value>
    An object which can retrieve a value given a key.
    NextIterator<Value>
    Interface for iteration where hasNext() is replaced by the semantics that null represents the end of iteration
    Prependable<Value>
    An object, often a collection or related type, to which objects can be prepended.
    Sectionable<Value,Section extends Addable<Value> & Indexable<Value>>
    Retrieves different subsections from an Indexable.
    Sequence<Value>
    A sequence of values returned by Sequence.asIterator() and Sequence.asIterator(Matcher).
    Sized
    An object (usually some sort of collection or store of values) which has a Sized.size().
    SpaceLimited
    An object that can store a limited number of values.
    WriteIndexable<Value>
    An indexable object is Indexable, but also supports setting values.
